This paper is about visual tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques, such as regularization and optimization, to improve tracking performance, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses hand-crafted features and CNN features, which are common in multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the proposed method, which could also place it in the robotics (cs.RO) category.
